From ad856b9efdc8396e2f2c3056c83062ac2c8c3958 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: CarolinePascal <caroline8.pascal@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:52:29 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] perf(rbd): per-env parallelism + capture-safe dispatch
 (bit-identical)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

GPU-side optimizations for the batched multibody rollout, all verified
bit-identical (biped gather err 0.0). Lifts the native-CUDA biped from
45k -> 60.8k env/s @ N=8192 (Isaac gap 4.8x -> 3.3x).

Per-env parallelism (the plateau was per-env serial work, not dispatch):
- broad_phase/{lbvh,narrow_phase}: the three threads(1) "*_init_dispatch"
  kernels serially scanned all N batches in ONE thread to compute an indirect
  grid size (O(N) anti-scaling). Replaced with single-workgroup threads(256)
  parallel max-reductions (shared helper highest_len_over_batches): 155x/call.
- multibody/contact_constraints: gpu_mb_finalize_contact_constraints made
  cooperative threads(32) — lane-split over the independent per-constraint LU
  back-solves (no barriers, disjoint writes): ~11.6x/call.
- multibody/joint_constraints: gpu_mb_init_solve_joint_with_bias split into a
  serial metadata-discovery walk (defer_column) -> barrier -> parallel
  back-solve phase (compute_joint_columns_par, finalize-style s += lanes) ->
  barrier -> lane-0 Gauss-Seidel PGS: ~4.5x/call. (Gating the back-solve inside
  the serial walk does NOT parallelize: SIMT lockstep runs one lane per slot.)

Dispatch / capture (lib.rs, solver.rs, pipeline.rs, radix_sort, coloring,
warmstart, joint, multibody): fixed-grid dispatch is now the backend-aware
default (ON for CUDA — kills the indirect host round-trip / GPU drain,
physics_encode 1114->25ms; OFF for WebGPU; BIPED_FIXED_GRID overrides) via
set_fixed_dispatch_grid_default(is_cuda) in pipeline from_rapier. Plus the
radix-sort ThreadCount-vs-Grid capture fix, color-counter fusion, and
max_colors plumbing from the capture-enablement work.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
